功能对等理论主要通过以下四个标准来指导翻译实践:
(1)传达信息;
(2)传达原作的精神和风格;
(3)语言通顺，符合译文的语法规则和表达习惯;
(4)读者反应相似。翻译为英文

The theory of functional equivalence primarily guides translation practice through the following four standards:

1. Conveying the information;
2. Conveying the spirit and style of the original work;
3. Making the language smooth and in compliance with the grammar and expression habits of the target language;
4. Producing a similar response in the reader.

These standards are used to ensure that the translation maintains a functional equivalence between the source and target language, and that the final product is not only accurate but also compatible with the target culture and language.

Introduction of The Certification Center for International Commerce of CCPIT Guangdong

Established and operated under the supervision of the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT) Guangdong Committee and Guangdong Chamber of International Commerce (CCOIC Guangdong), the Certification Center for International Commerce of CCPIT Guangdong (the Center) provides business certification,authentication and training services. To expand and improve its services, with the supervision, support and cooperation of the relevant organizations, the Center is also functioned as CCPIT FTA Guangdong Service Center, CCPIT Guangdong Pilot Free Trade Zone (FTZ) Service Center, CCPIT Guangdong and CCIC* Guangdong Cooperation Center, Guangdong Office of the Standardization Technological Committee of CCPIT Commercial Committee for New Business Forms and Models of Foreign Trade, Guangdong Standardization Service Center of CCPIT Commercial Committee,and the CCPIT Guangdong Standardization Technological Committee for New Business Forms and Models of Foreign Trade.

Services of the Center includes:
1.To issue CCPIT certificates for foreign trade, such as: General Certificate of Origin,Preference Certificate of Origin,international commercial certificates, the consul authentication, ATA Carnet, Certificate of Free Sale, Brand Certificate of Chinese Export Commodities, Enterprise Credit Evaluation by CCPIT, Certificate of Service Provider,etc.;
2.To be an agent for notarial certificate consular authentication and visa application;
3.To establish various standard systems,including to set up projects and carry out research and formulation of international,national,industrial and organizational standards;  to provide education,training and international exchanges on standardization; to participate in professional standardization technological organizations,the evaluation and comparison on the levels of standards,and enterprise trusteeship (custody of standards), etc;
4.To provide services of various product and system certifications home and abroad, inspection and examination, product traceability,supply chain management, and relevant technical consulting services; to provide response measures on technological and trade barriers;
5.To promote and explain the rules and regulations of FTA; to introduce and interpret the policies of RCEP and taking the advantage of RCEP;to provide solutions and plans on tariffs;
6.To arrange various international business training, including analysis of international cargo trade access rules,promotion and implementation of standards of domestic sale of export products,interpretation and analysis on export control act of China and America,export of epidemic prevention materials,certificate of force majeure, cross border financial service solutions,etc.;
7.To organize and carry out policy research on Pilot Free Trade Zone (FTZ) and promotion of important projects; to organize enterprise-government symposiums, industrial forums, and business matching activities for enterprises home and abroad;
8.To provide commercial legal advice, including intellectual property rights, patent and trade mark agency, etc.;翻译为英文
